Hico Independent School District
March 13 at 5:46 PM ·

IMPORTANT MESSAGE FROM HICO ISD:

In an effort to ensure the safety of our students and staff, Hico ISD campuses will be closed March 16th-20th. In order to meet the requirements of the Texas Education Agency, we will offer remote instruction which will be ready on Thursday morning through Google classroom or homework packets that can be picked up at your campus. More details on how to access the instruction will be provided early next week.

In addition, the UIL has suspended all sporting and academic activities through March 29th so there will be no games, practices or contests next week.

Also, the Jenkins Center facility will be closed to the public until further notice.

Thank you for your continued support. We will keep you updated as the situation develops.

Sincerely,
Jon Hartgraves

It is with heavy hearts that the Hico Athletic Booster Club extends our deepest sympathy and condolences to the family and friends of Mr. Bud Young. Mr. Bud's memorial service will be held tomorrow at 3pm at the Duffau Baptist Church.
What an amazing addition he has been to the Hico Athletic Booster Club organization. His presence will be greatly missed yet our memories of his love for all our Hico kids will continue for years to come. His example of always lending a helping hand will forever be implanted in the minds and hearts of our Athletic Booster Club members.
Thank you Mr. Bud for always backing your Hico kids.

From Coach Vosburg: HHS will host a meet on Thursday March 12th, it will be a full track meet to make up for the High School meet that was cancelled to due bad weather. The track meet will begin at 3:30 pm with field events and running events starting at 5 pm. We should have excellent weather for this meet, so what better way to work on your tan and support our Hico athletes than to volunteer on Thursday. I'm going to start from scratch with a workers list and need anybody that would be available to please email me with your preference of event or job to begin a sign up sheet. Again we would not be able to do this without you and thanks in advance for your help and continued support of the Tigers and Lady Tigers.

Nolan Vosburg
nvosburg@hico-isd.net

From Coach Vosburg: HHS will host a meet on Thursday March 12th, it will be a full track meet to make up for the High School meet that was cancelled to due bad weather. The track meet will begin at 3:30 pm with field events and running events starting at 5 pm. We should have excellent weather for this meet, so what better way to work on your tan and support our Hico athletes than to volunteer on Thursday. I'm going to start from scratch with a workers list and need anybody that would be available to please email me with your preference of event or job to begin a sign up sheet. Again we would not be able to do this without you and thanks in advance for your help and continued support of the Tigers and Lady Tigers.

Nolan Vosburg
nvosburg@hico-isd.net

Friday night our Football team will play their Area Championship game at 7:30pm against Honey Grove at Ferris High School. A map is on our website.

Send-off @ 2:30 at High Hchool. Meet in the back parking lot.

We will be hosting a playoff game here on Saturday. Miford vs Cherokee. We will need help in the concession stand, please contact Alma (254-979-0677)

We still have a couple L-XL-2XL tshirts leftover.

Monday - JH Basketball vs Goldthwaite. Girls in Hico, Boys in Goldthwaite

Tuesday - JV & Varsity Basketball in Clifton.

post_text:
Booster Club meeting tonight @ 6:00pm in the Jenkins Center. Please come out and join us!!

Congrats to Kelsey Warren. She placed 9th at the State Cross Country meet. Way to go Kelsey!

Our football team beat Goldthwaite Friday night and tied for the District Championship. Due to the "points rule" they will be positioned 2nd in the playoff bracket. They will play Kerens on Friday at 7pm at Waco Robinson. There is a map on the Hico website. This is exciting times for the Hico Tigers. Come cheer them on Friday!

There will be a pep rally bonfire Thursday night at Keith and Ladonna Turner's starting at 6:30pm. Come ready to yell and have some fun.

Our Lady Tigers played terrific Friday in their volleyball playoff game, while it was not enough to win, they have had an amazing season!! Congratulations Lady Tigers!!!

Basketball:
Tomorrow (Tuesday) in Eastland - JV & Varsity Girls.
Thursday - JH Girls here vs. San Saba
Friday - Varsity Girls only starting at 3:30pm here against Millsap.

The booster club is taking orders for High School Football and Junior High football Roster t-shirts. If you are interested you may email Mrs. Stegall at sstegall@hico-isd.net. Please be sure to designate whether you want the high school or junior high roster.
The shirts are short sleeve and will be similar to the Tiger Camp shirts that the boys got this summer (light blue with a red H). Orders are due by Friday to ensure that you get it for the first home game.

Hico will be hosting four track meets in the next few weeks. We desparately need you to help out in our concession stand. Please contact me if you are available to help. We like to get plenty of volunteers so we can work around all those who want to watch their child participate in their events.
Thank you for always being willing to help out to support our Hico Tigers and Lady Tigers! You are really appreciated!!!

Track Meet dates:
March 1 - High School
March 2 - Jr High
March 8 - High School
March 9 - Jr High

Concession stand shift hours will be scheduled between 2:30-8:00. Contact

post_text:
Hi all....
Tonight's Basketball games against Dubin are very important games for our Hico Tigers and Lady Tigers!! Bring on the SPIRIT!! Come show them your support and cheer them on!!!!!
And, while you are here, consider helping out in the concession stand....PLEASE!!! We sure could use your help. If you are excited about getting involved in all the fun, eager to serve, or just available please give me a call.
Also, as an extra bonus tonight, Project Graduation is hosting a delicious Mexican Dinner Fundraiser. YUM!!
So....bring along a friend, spouse, parent for a great time at Hico High School tonight.
Thanks....hope to see you here!!
